---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CTAButton from "../components/CTAButton.astro";
import InfoCard from "../components/InfoCard.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About PCB | BuiltByPCB"
  description="About PCB, a CISSP-certified security and cloud operations professional transitioning from mission-critical operations into security leadership."
  active="about"
>
  <main id="top" class="bg-slate-950 px-4 py-10 md:px-6 md:py-12 text-slate-100 md:py-16">
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
      <p class="mb-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan-300 sm:text-sm sm:tracking-[0.3em]">
        About PCB
      </p>

      <h1 class="max-w-4xl text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-6xl">
        From mission-critical operations to security leadership.
      </h1>

      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-slate-300">
        PCB is a CISSP-certified cybersecurity and operations professional with
        12+ years supporting high-availability environments where uptime,
        documentation, escalation discipline, and risk communication matter.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <CTAButton href="/resume">
          View Resume Tracks
        </CTAButton>

        <CTAButton href="/case-studies" variant="secondary">
          View Case Studies
        </CTAButton>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
        <InfoCard title="Where I Started">
          <p>
            My foundation is in 24/7 network and systems operations supporting
            mission-critical environments. That background shaped how I think:
            stabilize first, document clearly, communicate impact, and prevent recurrence.
          </p>
        </InfoCard>

        <InfoCard title="Where I Am Now">
          <p>
            With CISSP, Security+, and active Public Trust experience, I am focused
            on roles that connect security operations, incident response, risk,
            resilience, and governance.
          </p>
        </InfoCard>

        <InfoCard title="Where I’m Going">
          <p>
            My long-term direction is cloud security and ISSO/ISSE-aligned work:
            securing systems, validating controls, improving visibility, and helping
            organizations make better risk decisions.
          </p>
        </InfoCard>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-5xl">
      <InfoCard title="Professional Identity">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p>
            I operate best where security, reliability, and operational pressure intersect.
            My experience is not purely theoretical; it comes from environments where
            incidents require coordination, communication, documentation, and follow-through.
          </p>

          <p>
            BuiltByPCB exists to document that progression: from NOC and mission-critical
            operations into incident response, GRC/risk, cloud governance, and security leadership.
          </p>
        </div>
      </InfoCard>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-cyan-300/30 bg-slate-900 p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Current Career Lanes</h2>

        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
          <a
            href="/resume/security-operations"
            class="rounded-2xl border border-cyan-300 p-5 text-cyan-300 transition hover:bg-cyan-300 hover:text-slate-950"
          >
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Primary</p>
            <h3 class="mt-3 font-semibold">Security Operations / IR</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm">
              Incident response, monitoring, escalation, and operational resilience.
            </p>
          </a>

          <a
            href="/resume/grc-risk"
            class="rounded-2xl border border-cyan-300 p-5 text-cyan-300 transition hover:bg-cyan-300 hover:text-slate-950"
          >
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Target</p>
            <h3 class="mt-3 font-semibold">GRC / Risk</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm">
              Controls, evidence, remediation tracking, audit readiness, and risk communication.
            </p>
          </a>

          <a
            href="/resume/cloud-security"
            class="rounded-2xl border border-cyan-300 p-5 text-cyan-300 transition hover:bg-cyan-300 hover:text-slate-950"
          >
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Destination</p>
            <h3 class="mt-3 font-semibold">Cloud Security / ISSO</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm">
              Shared responsibility, continuous monitoring, cloud governance, and ISSO support.
            </p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-cyan-300/30 bg-slate-900 p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">What BuiltByPCB Shows</h2>

        <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-slate-300">
          <li>• Practical incident response and operational coordination experience</li>
          <li>• Security documentation and audit-ready thinking</li>
          <li>• Progression from operations into GRC, cloud security, and ISSO-aligned work</li>
          <li>• Technical projects that demonstrate automation, analysis, and cloud/security growth</li>
          <li>• A professional platform that can evolve into consulting and authority-building</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <CTAButton href="/projects">
            View Projects
          </CTAButton>

          <CTAButton href="/#contact" variant="secondary">
            Contact PCB
          </CTAButton>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-6xl px-6 pb-4 text-center">
      <CTAButton href="#top" variant="secondary">
        Back to Top ↑
      </CTAButton>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>